- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper presents an algorithm for constructing the LZ-End parsing of a given string. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of LZ77, a well-known compression algorithm based on information theory. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses the time and space complexity of the algorithm. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the streaming fashion of constructing the parsing, which could be relevant to distributed or parallel computing. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also less likely but possible as the paper mentions experimental comparisons to other LZ77-based analogs, which could be relevant to network analysis.
